hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'm doing a phd in chemistry creationpharm.biz Japan, the nation that could build a large and super high-tech military almost overnight and again dominate the region as it did about eight decades ago, is considered a cyber-toilet? Give me a break. No doubt the Japanese military have secret very close relationships with Japanese industrial high-tech to thwart real cyber-snoopers with serious warnings that they will be absolutely crushed unless they stop. And they do. Cyber-death can be savage, I’m told. And US security complaining and wanting closer ties and agreeing is like opening your doors to somebody you don’t trust.
